<Base title="Transformer Temperature Controller OEM Options" description="Review configurable transformer temperature controller items including range, contacts, output, power, capillary, mounting and remote display requirements."><section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Configuration support</p><h1>OEM and Project Customization</h1><p>Define the measurable configuration items that make an OTI, WTI or monitoring device fit a transformer project.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="grid two"><article class="card metric"><h2>Measurement and scale</h2><p>Confirm the temperature range, scale markings, accuracy class and whether the value is top oil or simulated winding temperature.</p></article><article class="card metric"><h2>Contacts and control</h2><p>Define contact quantity, duty, switching sequence and assignment to cooling, alarm or trip circuits.</p></article><article class="card metric"><h2>Remote interfaces</h2><p>Specify Pt100, 4-20 mA, RS485 or a compatible remote display together with supply and scaling.</p></article><article class="card metric"><h2>Mechanical fit</h2><p>Confirm enclosure, mounting, bulb, thread, insertion depth, capillary length, cable entry and environmental conditions.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section tint"><article class="container prose"><h2>What can be reviewed for a project?</h2><p>Available product families show several ranges, contact quantities, signals and capillary lengths. A project review compares the requested configuration with current model availability. It does not assume every possible combination is a standard item.</p><p>For replacement work, send the full existing model code, dial photograph, nameplate, terminal diagram and mounting dimensions. The review identifies whether a direct match is available or whether the panel, pocket, wiring or remote input must change.</p><h2>What should the inquiry contain?</h2><p>Include transformer type and rating, measured value, preferred model, scale, switch functions, contact voltage and load, remote signal, supply, capillary, bulb and thread, installation environment, quantity, destination country and requested delivery date. Attach project drawings when possible.</p><h2>What remains subject to confirmation?</h2><p>The current datasheet, outline drawing, wiring diagram, communication details and commercial terms must be confirmed for the selected configuration. This website does not invent certification, lead-time or customization claims that are not supported by the applicable documents.</p></article></section><EmailCTA title="Send a Configuration Requirement" subject="Transformer temperature controller OEM and customization request" /></Base>
